710520f-b.title: Manhattan: 10th Avenue - 29th Street (West)
710520f-b.text:
Tenth Avenue, east side, from West 29th to 30th Streets,
showing the New York Cettral Railroad's hmilk shed. This ex-
tends eastward to 9th Avenue. In 1931 this site is to be cleared
for the new U. S. Parcel Post Building.
About 1930
Views 1,2,3,4
P. L. Sperr

710521f-b.title: Manhattan: 10th Avenue - 29th Street (West)
710521f-b.text:
Tenth Avenue, at the N. E. corner of West 29th Street, showing
the milk shed and yards of the New York Central Railroad. This
occupies the entire block east to 9tb Avenue and extending from
29th to 30tH Streets. In 1931, this site will be cleared for the new
U. S. Parcel Post Building.
Note in the background of View 2, the Empire State Building
emerging from the horizon.
May 12, 1930
September 8, 1930
P. L. Sperr

710519f-a.title: Manhattan: 10th Avenue - 29th Street (West)
710519f-a.text:
Tenth Avenue, at the N. E. corner of W. 29th Street, showing
the vew York Central Railroad's milk unloading yard site being pre-
pared for the U. S. Parcel Post Building that is to rise here. This
block site extends from 10th to 9th Avenues, between 29th to 30th
Streets. Vote the Empire State Building dominating the background.
The white structure to the left is the recently erected Sears Roe-
buck and Company building at the S. E. corner of 9th Avenue and
W. 31st Street. This arose concurrent with the Empire State Build-
ing.
June 2, 1931
Views 1,2
P. L. Sperr

710517f-a.title: Manhattan: 10th Avenue - 29th Street
710517f-a.text:
Tenth Avenue at N. E. corner of 29th Street, showing at left,
excavation for Parcel Post Office.
Empire State Building in centre background.
June 2, 1931.
P.L. Sperr,Photographer.

710523f-b.title: Manhattan: 10th Avenue - 29th Street (West)
710523f-b.text:
Tenth Avenue, worth from W. 29th Street, showing "Railroad
Avenue" and its pedestrian bridge at 30t) Street. On the right
are the milk unloading yards of the New York Central Railroad.
This site was later improved with the U. S. Parcel Post Building
(see view 2). In the background is the Master Printers Buuilding
at 34th Street.
View 2, being later shows the new Post Office building and
the elevated roadbed of the New York Central Railroad entering
same. The street level has returned to civic use at this date.
This view is at 30th Street.
March 24, 1929
May 30, 1934
P. L. Sperr

711944f-a.title: Manhattan: 29th Street (West) - 10th Avenue
711944f-a.text:
516-526 West 29th Street, south side, west of Tenth Avenue.
No. 516 and 524 are one-story frame buildings and No. 520 is a
three-story frame building.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
